metadata.name: PixelShifter #358
metadata.description:
Two simple geometric shapes repeated and slowly oscillating. 
Produced to celebrate a year of FXHash. 
Congratulations to the team and thanks to everyone who has supported me.
50% of Primary and secondary will go the the Processing foundation.

Features include 6 types of shape
Black or white background and 15 varying palettes

metadata.name: CRAYONS #150
metadata.description:
Sometimes we like the feeling of being citizens of the places we visit. Our senses adapt to capture in detail the signs of the environment. It is then when we begin to breathe the color that surrounds us and places us in that unique setting.

This is how this inspired collection is born and grows, the colors that enchant us as children on a sheet of paper and now serve to paint every place we visit.

The 6 color palettes of this collection aim to transport us to all those places.

Paris: Its pastel tones strolling along the Trocadero on the banks of the Seine.

Berlin: How to tell the story with color in the graffiti of the East Side Gallery and the wall.

Mexico: Its flavor is in the rainbow of its embroideries, alebrijes and altars.

Kenya: Sunrises and sunsets that impregnate the retina with the tones of the savannah.

Costa Rica: Pure life, pure green, from gentle to intense Monte Lluvioso.

Colombia: Seas of flowers flood the streets with colors and aromas celebrating the Feria De Las Flores

High-resolution png downloads are available by pressing number keys 1 (3000px), 2 (6000px), or 3 (9000px).

metadata.name: Orchard #91
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

metadata.description:

metadata.name: Equanimity #215
metadata.description: Equanimity shows the algorithm in its search for balance in color and composition. All mints eventually converge to a stable state. If this takes longer than 40 seconds, the captured thumbnail will be different from the final result. Implemented in 5773 hand-crafted characters of JS code. Forever limited to 496 unique editions living on the Tezos blockchain. London - December 2021.
